# Angular: Template in Separate File

Always put Angular component templates in a dedicated `.html` file next to the component. Do **not** use inline `template: \`...\`` in the `@Component` decorator.

## Rule

- Use **`templateUrl`** pointing to a same-name `.html` file (e.g. `./login.component.html`).
- Do **not** use inline **`template`** with a template string in the component class.

## Example

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - inline template
@Component({
  selector: 'app-login',
  template: `
    <div class="container">...</div>
  `,
})
export class LoginComponent {}

// ✅ GOOD - separate file
@Component({
  selector: 'app-login',
  templateUrl: './login.component.html',
})
export class LoginComponent {}
```

## File layout

- `login.component.ts` – component class only, with `templateUrl: './login.component.html'`
- `login.component.html` – template markup

Apply this pattern to all Angular components (including those with `template:` today). When creating or editing components, create or update the `.html` file and reference it via `templateUrl`.
